topicSummary: Migraine is a primary episodic headache disorder. It is characterized by severe headaches with symptoms such as photophobia, nausea and vomiting

latestChanges.title: Reviewed
latestChanges.body: A literature search was conducted in March 2019 to identify evidence-based guidelines, UK policy, systematic reviews, and key randomized controlled trials published since the last revision of the topic. Minor changes to the recommendations have been made in line with updated guidance from the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence NICE, 2012 (updated 2015) and the Scottish Intercollegiate Guidelines Network SIGN,2018.
